
[1]umbrage

   UM'BRAGE, n. [L. umbra, a shade.]

   1. A shade; a screen of trees; as the umbrage of woods.

   2. Shadow; shade; slight appearance.

   The opinion carries no show of truth nor umbrage of reason on its side.
   [See Shadow.]

   3. Suspicion of injury; offense; resentment. The court of France took
   umbrage at the conduct of spain.
